<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1976,2039]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,150,249]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="563" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson, J." box="[151,340,1976,2003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" pagination="353 - 578" refId="ref4837" refString="Thomson, J. (1865) Diagnoses d'especes nouvelles qui seront decrites dans l'appendix du systema cerambycidarum. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Liege, 19, 353 - 578." type="journal article" year="1865">Thomson (1865)</bibRefCitation>
briefly described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1865" box="[549,708,1976,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lilliputanus">
<emphasis box="[549,708,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">L. lilliputanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows (translated): “ 
<collectingCountry box="[995,1112,1976,2002]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. Length, 3.0 mm, width, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. Brown, punctate; elytra with two oblique grayish pubescent band [considering both elytra], then light brown [toward apex]; legs yellow with brown maculae; species very distinct.” Apparently, it is not a true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" box="[1232,1360,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1232,1360,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="563">Leptostylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the photograph and original description do not allow for the recognition of the genus. I was not able to find a species that matches 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1865" box="[387,544,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lilliputanus">
<emphasis box="[387,544,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="563">L. lilliputanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in any known genus of American 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1089,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Acanthocinini" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Acanthocinini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
